# Public-release path allowlist (fail-closed).
#
# The single source of truth for WHAT MAY EXIST in the public repo. Consumed by:
#   - scripts/build-public-release.sh  (what to copy private -> public staging)
#   - scripts/check-public-release.py  (path layer: any tree file not matching a
#                                        glob here is a violation -> exit 2)
#   - the public repo's CI leak-guard job
# Because copy-set == check-set == this file, the two cannot drift.
#
# FAIL-CLOSED: anything not listed here is PRIVATE by default. Adding a glob is a
# conscious decision to publish. Prefer narrow globs over broad ones.
#
# Format: <glob> | <reason>   (relative to repo root; '**' recurses; '#' comments;
# blank lines ignored). Globs are expanded with pathlib semantics.

# --- Engine + tests (the framework code) ---
src/**/* | governance + context-engine source (domain-agnostic)
tests/**/* | test suite (de-domained by scripts/dedomain-public.py before publish)
pyproject.toml | package metadata
requirements.lock | pinned deps
Dockerfile | container build (rebuilds a meta-only index from documents/)
docker-compose.yml | container orchestration
.dockerignore | excludes index/ from the image (index rebuilt in-container)

# --- Infra / CI / enforcement ---
.github/**/* | CI workflows (SHA-pinned, least-privilege)
.claude/hooks/**/* | governance enforcement hooks (framework)
.claude/agents/**/* | subagent definitions (verified clean of domain/client refs)
.pre-commit-config.yaml | local pre-commit hooks
.gitignore | ignore rules
.editorconfig | editor config

# --- Framework skills (canonical home = global-skills/) ---
global-skills/**/* | framework-owned skills (content-enhancer hotel examples scrubbed pre-publish)

# --- Meta-framework content (NOT subject-matter domains) ---
documents/constitution.md | constitutional principles (meta)
documents/rules-of-procedure.md | governance methods (meta)
documents/ai-instructions.md | framework activation loader (meta)
documents/failure-mode-registry.md | engineering failure-mode registry (meta)
documents/test-failure-mode-map.md | derived test->FM coverage map (meta)
documents/tiers.json | universal-floor / critical-5 config (runtime-required, meta)
documents/agents/**/* | canonical agent templates (meta)
documents/.public-allowlist | this file (the allowlist is itself public)

# --- Reference library: EXCLUDED from public ---
# The reference library is domain-KEYED (extractor scans reference-library/<domain>/
# per registered domain). With no domains registered in public, entries are never
# indexed, and per "all domains private" the whole domain-keyed library is private.
# (No reference-library/** globs here -> not copied. A future public-only generic
# reference set could be added if desired.)

# --- Release tooling that the PUBLIC repo needs (for its own CI guard) ---
scripts/check-public-release.py | the leak-guard itself (runs in public CI)
scripts/check-citations.py | citation-form guard (public CI citation-check job + its test)
documents/.citation-allowlist | citation allowlist read by check-citations.py

# --- Root docs ---
README.md | project overview (domain table reduced to constitution at publish)
ARCHITECTURE.md | system design
SPECIFICATION.md | requirements
API.md | API reference
EXECUTION-FRAMEWORK.md | execution methodology
SECURITY.md | security model
INFLUENCES.md | attribution
AGENTS.md | agent/project overview
CLAUDE.md | Claude Code governance instructions (framework; verified leak-clean)
LICENSE | Apache-2.0 (code)
LICENSE-CONTENT | CC-BY-NC-ND-4.0 (framework content)
SBOM.md | software bill of materials
RELEASE.md | public/private split + leak-remediation runbook
